<br>
Also, Helen was definately dead when she appeared at the end. <br>
<br>
Personally, I think the horror of the candyman is the typical draw it has on legends. Everyone who ever went to a slumber party at a friend's house has heard stories similiar to it, the most famous of which is Bloody Mary (Mary, Queen of Scots who threw herself from her balcony back in the middle ages, repeat bloody mary three times at midnight while looking into a mirror in a darkened room and she'll appear and take you into her mirror). A sort of what if the stories like that were true? Also his ability to just stalk and ruin the life of his victims, getting people to think that they're the ones killing off the people they're close to. Candyman isn't a killer, but a destroyer. Even if you survive you'll be locked in an insane asylum for the rest of your life.<br>
<br>
